The paper proposes a framework for improving the Deep Q Network (DQN) algorithm, which is a popular reinforcement learning method. The focus is on the probability distribution of the value function parameters, which suggests a connection to machine learning and statistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DL (Deep Learning). The paper also mentions the use of the algorithm on a Markov Decision Process (MDP), which suggests a connection to robotics and control, leading to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as possible sub-categories.
